{"questionId":"9069321","questionHtml":"<p>Calculate the value of the equilibrium constant, <em>K</em>, at 298 K. Use sections 1 and 2 of the data booklet.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>K</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>⟨</mo><mo>⟨</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>∆</mo><mi>G</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>R</mi><mo>.</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>⟩</mo><mo>⟩</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>33000</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>31</mn><mi>x</mi><mn>298</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>/</mo><mo>«</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>»</mo><mn>13</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>K</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>13</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup></math>&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Award <strong>[2]</strong> for correct final answer.</em></p>\n<p><em>Accept answers in the range 4.4×10<sup>5</sup> to 6.2×10<sup>5</sup> (arises from rounding of ln K).</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9069321","referenceCode":"22M.2.hl.TZ1.3c(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate the value of the equilibrium constant, K, at 298 K. Use sections 1 and 2 of the data booklet.","paper":"2","level":"hl","questionNumber":"c(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 17: Equilibrium","17.1 The equilibrium law","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 17: Equilibrium"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}